Item #: SCP-5031

Object Class: Safe

Special Containment Procedures: SCP-5031 is implanted with a tracking device and is currently resides in a 6.1 m by 6.1 m (12.2 pw by 12.2 pw) room at Minimal Security Site 17. SCP-5031 is currently allowed Class 3 (restricted) socialization privileges with approved site personnel, granted based on continued good behavior and cooperation with Foundation personnel.

Description: SCP-5031 is a sapient bipedal tailless furless (mostly) plantigrade male creature, 185 cm (15.1 pw) tall and 80 kg, with blue eyes and pale smooth skin, brown fur on top of its head, short and dark - on a bottom of its flat, snoutless, face and scattered across the body in marginal amounts.

DNA test results show zero matches with any known species, however, some sequences are matching with Haplorhini suborder. MRI and CT scannings show little no difference with usual canidian anatomy, mostly in size, shape and placement of organs.

Physically Subject doesn't show any supernatural results in terms of strength and speed, and barely passes average High School Physical tests. However, in terms of stamina it overcomes the test baseline at [___]%, lacking of fur and more effective cooling system makes him more resilient to high temperature conditions - at [___]%, if provided with water - [____]%.

SCP-5031 claims his name is [____] [_______], [__] years old, was born in [__].[__].19[__] in [______], [______]. There was found no known cities and countries existing or ever existed with such a name, as well as SCP-5031 claimed name doesn't appear in any available data bases. Subject insists he's familiar with Foundation and canidians, "but he's never thought they're real", and it seems in SCP-5031 homeworld SCP Foundation and bipedal canids don't exist and are nothing but a part of cultural phenomena.

Additional Notes: SCP-5031 was sighted in [______], [______] on April 28, 20[__], running naked and confused across the town. For any witness the event was claimed as a sci-fi movie location shooting "with practical effects for real life reactions".


Excerpt from Interview Log 5031-01

Interviewer: Dr. Laura Longtail, xenopsychologist

>Dr. Longtail: Please give a brief personal introduction, including date and place of birth, and your name.

>Dr. Longtail: One minute please... According to our data, there's no such a city or country existing or ever existed.

...
